{
  format: 1
  name: string-casefold-full-fold-differs-from-lower
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#expressions", "§6.5", "#annex-a", "§A.1"]
  tags: ["unicode"]
  note: '''
    §6.5: `string.casefold` "applies the corresponding Unicode default ...
    casefold operation" — the full (C+F) Unicode default case fold — while
    `string.lower` applies the Unicode default lowercase mapping. The two are
    NOT the same operation, and this case pins values where they diverge, so a
    tautology is impossible and folding-as-lowercasing would be caught:

      - LATIN SMALL LETTER SHARP S (ß, U+00DF): default case fold maps it to
        the two scalars "ss" (CaseFolding.txt `00DF; F; 0073 0073`), whereas
        default lowercase leaves ß unchanged. So casefold("Maße") = "masse"
        but lower("Maße") = "maße".
      - GREEK SMALL LETTER FINAL SIGMA (ς, U+03C2): default case fold maps it
        to GREEK SMALL LETTER SIGMA (σ, U+03C3) (CaseFolding.txt `03C2; C;
        03C3`), whereas default lowercase leaves the already-lowercase final
        sigma unchanged. So casefold("ὈΔΥΣΣΕΎΣ" tail) diverges; here
        casefold("ΟΔΟΣ") = "οδοσ" while lower("ΟΔΟΣ") = "οδος" (capital sigma
        lowercases to non-final σ, but a pre-existing final ς only folds).

    `string.casefold` is a core built-in string utility (§16.1 `string`
    namespace), usable in the database-evaluated computed-value position
    (§16.5). Both computed fields are read from a public view; the folded and
    lowered forms are asserted exactly.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.casefold@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      names: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        name: "text"
        folded: "= string.casefold(.name)"
        lowered: "= string.lower(.name)"
      }
      $public: {
        by_id: { $view: ".names { id, name, folded, lowered, $sort: [id] }" }
      }
    }
    $data: {
      names: {
        r1: { name: "Maße" }
        r2: { name: "ΟΔΟΣ" }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { watch: "public.by_id", id: "w1",
      expect_init: { value: [
        { id: "r1", name: "Maße", folded: "masse", lowered: "maße" }
        { id: "r2", name: "ΟΔΟΣ", folded: "οδοσ", lowered: "οδος" }
      ] } }
  ]
}
